            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat with 1/2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated</strong> <strong>hake fillet[s] </strong>with a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and a couple of splashes of <strong>cold</strong> <strong>water </strong>and cook, covered, for 3-4 min on each side or until cooked through – this is your <strong>spiced hake</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "order": 5,
