            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the fish is cooked, transfer it to a clean board and return the pan and any <strong>remaining juices</strong> to a low heat</p><p>Add your <strong>harissa paste </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)<strong> </strong>and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> to the pan and mix it all together</p><p>Squeeze in the<strong> </strong>juice of<strong> half</strong> your<strong> lemon[s] </strong>and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>– this is your <strong>warm harissa dressing</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining lemon </strong>into 1 wedge per person</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
